   ### Root Cause Summary
   The program fails because `abi::__cxa_demangle` is called on non-mangled C++
   symbols (e.g., `int`, `std::string`), which causes `status != 0`,
   `realnameString = nullptr`, and then a dangling pointer or
   `std::runtime_error` is thrown, caught, and results in `exit(8)`.
   
   ### Best Fix: Do Not Call `abi::__cxa_demangle` on Known Non-Mangled Names
   Add a guard:
   ```cpp
   // only demangle if name contains template or complex mangled structure
   if (strchr(input_buffer, '_') == nullptr) {
       realnameString = input_buffer;
   } else {
       // proceed with demangling
       realnameString = abi::__cxa_demangle(input_buffer, output_buffer, &length, &status);
       if (status != 0) {
           realnameString = input_buffer;
       } else {
           realnameString = output_buffer;
       }
   }
   ```
   
   This prevents demangling on simple names, avoiding failure.
   
